{"article_id":"wnxXNEzB9b9GJf5g","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Donald Trump waves","depth":6},{"id":1,"text":"as he walks out from the White House in Washington , DC","depth":6},{"id":2,"text":"( Reuters :","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"Yuri Gripas )","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"Up until now , veiled orders have not been thought the equivalent of obstruction .","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"On April 10 , 2016 , President Obama publicly stated","depth":12},{"id":6,"text":"that Hillary Clinton had shown \" carelessness \"","depth":13},{"id":7,"text":"in using a private e-mail server","depth":14},{"id":8,"text":"to handle classified information ,","depth":14},{"id":9,"text":"but he insisted","depth":12},{"id":10,"text":"that she had not intended to endanger national security","depth":13},{"id":11,"text":"( which is not an element of the relevant criminal statute ) .","depth":13},{"id":12,"text":"The president acknowledged","depth":12},{"id":13,"text":"that classified information had been transmitted via Secretary Clinton ' s server ,","depth":12},{"id":14,"text":"but he suggested","depth":12},{"id":15,"text":"that , in the greater scheme of things , its importance had been vastly overstated .","depth":12},{"id":16,"text":"On July 5 , 2016 , FBI director James Comey publicly stated","depth":12},{"id":17,"text":"that Clinton had been \" extremely careless \"","depth":13},{"id":18,"text":"in using a private email server","depth":14},{"id":19,"text":"to handle classified information ,","depth":14},{"id":20,"text":"but he insisted","depth":12},{"id":21,"text":"that she had not intended to endanger national security","depth":13},{"id":22,"text":"( which is not an element of the relevant criminal statute ) .","depth":13},{"id":23,"text":"The director acknowledged","depth":12},{"id":24,"text":"that classified information had been transmitted via Secretary Clinton ' s server ,","depth":12},{"id":25,"text":"but he suggested","depth":12},{"id":26,"text":"that , in the greater scheme of things , it was just a small percentage of the emails involved .","depth":12},{"id":27,"text":"Could there be more striking parallels ?","depth":8},{"id":28,"text":"A cynic might say","depth":9},{"id":29,"text":"that Obama had clearly signaled to the FBI and the Justice Department","depth":11},{"id":30,"text":"that he did not want Mrs. Clinton to be charged with a crime ,","depth":11},{"id":31,"text":"and that , with this not-so-subtle pressure in the air , the president ' s subordinates dropped the case","depth":11},{"id":32,"text":"- exactly what Obama wanted ,","depth":12},{"id":33,"text":"relying precisely on Obama ' s stated rationale .","depth":12},{"id":34,"text":"Of course , they ' re not yawning now .","depth":9},{"id":35,"text":"Now it is Donald Trump , not Barack Obama ,","depth":11},{"id":36,"text":"sending Comey signals .","depth":11},{"id":37,"text":"So now , such signals are a major issue","depth":11},{"id":38,"text":"- not merely of obstruction of justice ,","depth":12},{"id":39,"text":"but of high crimes and misdemeanors .","depth":12},{"id":40,"text":"Trump hysteria seems to be a permanent condition , a combustive compound of media-Democrat derangement","depth":6},{"id":41,"text":"surrounding a president","depth":7},{"id":42,"text":"who keeps providing derangement material .","depth":7},{"id":43,"text":"Let ' s try to keep our feet on the ground ,","depth":5},{"id":44,"text":"but with a commitment","depth":6},{"id":45,"text":"to get the evidence","depth":7},{"id":46,"text":"and go wherever it takes us .","depth":7},{"id":47,"text":"For now , we don ' t have much evidence .","depth":5},{"id":48,"text":"Essentially , we ' ve got single statement ,","depth":8},{"id":49,"text":"mined by the New York Times from a memo","depth":9},{"id":50,"text":"that no one outside a tight circle inside the FBI has seen","depth":10},{"id":51,"text":"- indeed , that the Times has not seen .","depth":10},{"id":52,"text":"According to anonymous sources ,","depth":10},{"id":53,"text":"the memo was written by then-FBI director Comey shortly after a private meeting with President Trump","depth":11},{"id":54,"text":"- only two of them in the room","depth":12},{"id":55,"text":"after Trump asked other officials to leave .","depth":12},{"id":56,"text":"This was on February 14 , the day after National Security Adviser Michael Flynn resigned over inaccurate statements","depth":10},{"id":57,"text":"he made to senior administration officials in recounting conversations","depth":11},{"id":58,"text":"he ' d had with Russian ambassador Sergei Kislyak .","depth":11},{"id":59,"text":"Trump is said to have told Comey ,","depth":10},{"id":60,"text":"\" I hope","depth":12},{"id":61,"text":"you can see your way clear to letting this go , to letting Flynn go .","depth":12},{"id":62,"text":"He is a good guy .","depth":12},{"id":63,"text":"I hope you can let this go . \"","depth":12},{"id":64,"text":"Other than telling us","depth":11},{"id":65,"text":"that Comey replied ,","depth":13},{"id":66,"text":"\" I agree","depth":13},{"id":67,"text":"he is a good guy , \"","depth":12},{"id":68,"text":"the Times provides no context of the conversation .","depth":11},{"id":69,"text":"Its report gives no indication","depth":12},{"id":70,"text":"of whether the memo provides such context .","depth":12},{"id":71,"text":"On its face , the statement does not amount to obstruction of justice .","depth":11},{"id":72,"text":"Trump could be said to be putting pressure on his subordinate ,","depth":12},{"id":73,"text":"just as Obama was putting pressure on his subordinates","depth":14},{"id":74,"text":"( Comey included )","depth":14},{"id":75,"text":"last April .","depth":13},{"id":76,"text":"But","depth":12},{"id":77,"text":"assuming the Times is right about the memo ,","depth":13},{"id":78,"text":"Trump did not order Comey to drop the case .","depth":13},{"id":79,"text":"In fact , Trump ' s statement is consistent","depth":13},{"id":80,"text":"with encouraging Comey to use his own judgment ,","depth":14},{"id":81,"text":"with the understanding","depth":15},{"id":82,"text":"that Trump hoped","depth":16},{"id":83,"text":"Comey would come out favorably to Flynn .","depth":16},{"id":84,"text":"But of course , also with the understanding","depth":14},{"id":85,"text":"that","depth":16},{"id":86,"text":"if Comey pushed to prosecute Flynn ,","depth":16},{"id":87,"text":"the president","depth":17},{"id":88,"text":"- who had the power","depth":18},{"id":89,"text":"to fire Comey -","depth":18},{"id":90,"text":"was going to be very unhappy .","depth":16},{"id":91,"text":"Just as President Obama would have been very unhappy , and in a position","depth":15},{"id":92,"text":"to fire Comey ,","depth":15},{"id":93,"text":"if Mrs. Clinton had been indicted .","depth":14},{"id":94,"text":"It is not frivolous to infer","depth":13},{"id":95,"text":"that Trump ' s statement to Comey was a veiled order .","depth":13},{"id":96,"text":"If that is your interpretation , though ,","depth":13},{"id":97,"text":"you can not avoid the conclusion","depth":14},{"id":98,"text":"that Obama ' s public statements were also veiled orders","depth":15},{"id":99,"text":"not to indict Clinton .","depth":15},{"id":100,"text":"Up until now , veiled orders have not been thought the equivalent of obstruction of justice .","depth":11},{"id":101,"text":"In light of what I ' ve previously contended","depth":13},{"id":102,"text":"( viz. , that obstruction of justice is a concept irrelevant to a counterintelligence investigation ) ,","depth":13},{"id":103,"text":"I must note here","depth":12},{"id":104,"text":"that concerns about obstruction of justice in the context of the reported Trump-Comey conversation are legitimate .","depth":11},{"id":105,"text":"That is because the conversation does not directly relate to the so-called Russia investigation ,","depth":10},{"id":106,"text":"which","depth":12},{"id":107,"text":"Comey has explained","depth":12},{"id":108,"text":"is a counterintelligence inquiry regarding Kremlin interference in the 2016 election .","depth":11},{"id":109,"text":"Rather , Trump and Comey were speaking about a criminal investigation of Flynn , ancillary to but separate from the Russia investigation .","depth":10},{"id":110,"text":"We are informed","depth":12},{"id":111,"text":"that a grand jury in Virginia is considering evidence of transactions","depth":13},{"id":112,"text":"involving Flynn ,","depth":13},{"id":113,"text":"although it is not clear that this was the case on February 14 ,","depth":12},{"id":114,"text":"when Trump and Comey spoke .","depth":12},{"id":115,"text":"There is good reason","depth":12},{"id":116,"text":"to believe","depth":13},{"id":117,"text":"that veiled orders ,","depth":14},{"id":118,"text":"while inappropriate ,","depth":15},{"id":119,"text":"are not criminal -","depth":15},{"id":120,"text":"i.e. , they do not rise to the level of prosecutable obstruction of justice .","depth":11},{"id":121,"text":"Obstruction can be a tough crime","depth":15},{"id":122,"text":"to prove .","depth":15},{"id":123,"text":"It is necessary to establish , beyond a reasonable doubt ,","depth":16},{"id":124,"text":"that the suspect acted corruptly","depth":17},{"id":125,"text":"in impeding or influencing a criminal investigation .","depth":17},{"id":126,"text":"That means acting with knowledge","depth":17},{"id":127,"text":"that one ' s conduct was unlawful ,","depth":17},{"id":128,"text":"and with a specific intent","depth":17},{"id":129,"text":"to undermine the truth-seeking function .","depth":17},{"id":130,"text":"Context is critical ,","depth":14},{"id":131,"text":"and we don ' t have it .","depth":14},{"id":132,"text":"All we know","depth":14},{"id":133,"text":"is that Trump hoped","depth":16},{"id":134,"text":"the criminal investigation would be dropped","depth":17},{"id":135,"text":"- but again , did not order it to be dropped -","depth":17},{"id":136,"text":"and vouched for Flynn ' s character .","depth":15},{"id":137,"text":"That may have been inappropriate under the circumstances ,","depth":14},{"id":138,"text":"but it was not corrupt .","depth":14},{"id":139,"text":"Comey surely found it awkward ,","depth":14},{"id":140,"text":"but he clearly did not perceive it as obstruction .","depth":14},{"id":141,"text":"The former director is a highly experienced and meritoriously decorated former prosecutor and investigator .","depth":16},{"id":142,"text":"He knows what obstruction of justice is .","depth":16},{"id":143,"text":"And the Jim Comey","depth":17},{"id":144,"text":"I ' ve known for 30 years","depth":17},{"id":145,"text":"would not stand for political interference in law enforcement .","depth":16},{"id":146,"text":"If he had understood Trump ' s remarks as a directive or , worse , a threat ,","depth":16},{"id":147,"text":"he would have resigned .","depth":16},{"id":148,"text":"It is not enough to say that he did not resign .","depth":15},{"id":149,"text":"Unlike the investigation of Mrs. Clinton , the investigation of Flynn has continued .","depth":13},{"id":150,"text":"Plus , Comey does not appear to have indicated to his subordinates , to his Justice Department superiors , or to Congress","depth":15},{"id":151,"text":"that he felt threatened .","depth":15},{"id":152,"text":"Deputy attorney general Rod Rosenstein and Comey ' s former deputy","depth":17},{"id":153,"text":"( now acting director )","depth":17},{"id":154,"text":"Andrew McCabe have not intimated , even vaguely ,","depth":16},{"id":155,"text":"that their investigative activities have been hampered .","depth":15},{"id":156,"text":"Again , the investigation is proceeding apace .","depth":9},{"id":157,"text":"There is no question","depth":11},{"id":158,"text":"that obstruction of justice is an impeachable offense .","depth":11},{"id":159,"text":"But media hyperventilating notwithstanding ,","depth":11},{"id":160,"text":"the basis","depth":13},{"id":161,"text":"for claiming at this point","depth":14},{"id":162,"text":"that President Trump obstructed justice","depth":14},{"id":163,"text":"is not there . . .","depth":12},{"id":164,"text":"unless you also think","depth":10},{"id":165,"text":"President Obama obstructed justice last April .","depth":10},{"id":166,"text":"Trump Firing James Comey Means","depth":3},{"id":167,"text":"it ' s Time for the President to Change","depth":3},{"id":168,"text":"- Andrew C. McCarthy is a senior policy fellow at the National Review Institute and a contributing editor of National Review .","depth":1}],"relations":[{"parent":337,"left":336,"right":168,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":336,"left":334,"right":335,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":334,"left":211,"right":333,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":211,"left":172,"right":210,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":172,"left":170,"right":171,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":170,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":171,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":210,"left":207,"right":209,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":207,"left":4,"right":206,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":206,"left":194,"right":205,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":194,"left":193,"right":27,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":193,"left":182,"right":192,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":182,"left":178,"right":181,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":178,"left":175,"right":177,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":175,"left":5,"right":174,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":174,"left":6,"right":173,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":173,"left":7,"right":8,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":177,"left":9,"right":176,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":176,"left":10,"right":11,"relation":"elaboration"